00:27:23.905 --> 00:27:27.300
Well, talking about the
versatility of the roles

00:27:27.300 --> 00:27:30.349
that you have played, and also
the different genres of movies

00:27:30.349 --> 00:27:31.890
you have done--
right, normally, when

00:27:31.890 --> 00:27:33.806
you think about Bollywood
stars, a lot of them

00:27:33.806 --> 00:27:35.610
carve a niche for themselves.

00:27:35.610 --> 00:27:40.170
They're known as Bollywood
chocolate actors or action

00:27:40.170 --> 00:27:42.270
heroes or dancers.

00:27:42.270 --> 00:27:44.114
And in the new
generation, these days

00:27:44.114 --> 00:27:45.280
it's a little bit different.

00:27:45.280 --> 00:27:46.210
They're more versatile.

00:27:46.210 --> 00:27:47.834
They can do a little
bit of everything.

00:27:47.834 --> 00:27:49.860
But honestly, you were
one of the first ones who

00:27:49.860 --> 00:27:52.560
broke that mold and
decided to do everything,

00:27:52.560 --> 00:27:55.940
from comedy in "Housefull"
to musical drama in "Rock

00:27:55.940 --> 00:27:59.510
On," to thrillers in
"Aankhen" and "Ek Ajnabee"

00:27:59.510 --> 00:28:01.030
to romantic movies--

00:28:01.030 --> 00:28:04.260
you had "Pyaar Ishq Aur
Mohabbat," "Dil Ka Rishta,"

00:28:04.260 --> 00:28:06.780
then you also did
"Raajneeti" and "Satyagraha,"

00:28:06.780 --> 00:28:08.040
which are political dramas.

00:28:08.040 --> 00:28:08.416
ARJUN RAMPAL: Yeah.

00:28:08.416 --> 00:28:09.750
And a villain in "Om Shanti Om."

00:28:09.750 --> 00:28:11.374
APRAJITA JAIN: Yeah,
you did a villain.

00:28:11.374 --> 00:28:12.480
You were a cop in a movie.

00:28:12.480 --> 00:28:15.270
Then now you're doing a
criminal turned a politician.

00:28:15.270 --> 00:28:16.920
How do you go about
deciding which

00:28:16.920 --> 00:28:18.250
roles you're going to take on?

00:28:18.250 --> 00:28:20.680
And how do you
prepare for those?

00:28:20.680 --> 00:28:22.410
ARJUN RAMPAL: You
know, actually,

00:28:22.410 --> 00:28:25.870
one of my main criteria
of signing a film really

00:28:25.870 --> 00:28:31.400
is that if I went out there
at the ticket counter,

00:28:31.400 --> 00:28:34.270
and if I was not in this
movie, would I go and watch

00:28:34.270 --> 00:28:36.460
this film regardless?

00:28:36.460 --> 00:28:38.360
And that's the first question.

00:28:38.360 --> 00:28:39.247
So that's the story.

00:28:39.247 --> 00:28:40.330
APRAJITA JAIN: User first.

00:28:40.330 --> 00:28:41.080
ARJUN RAMPAL: Huh?

00:28:41.080 --> 00:28:41.750
APRAJITA JAIN: User first.

00:28:41.750 --> 00:28:43.030
That's how Google thinks too.

00:28:43.030 --> 00:28:43.821
ARJUN RAMPAL: Yeah.

00:28:43.821 --> 00:28:46.390
So you have to, you know, say,
would I really want to be--

00:28:46.390 --> 00:28:48.340
would I watch it?

00:28:48.340 --> 00:28:51.550
Then the second one
is who the people are

00:28:51.550 --> 00:28:53.320
that you're associating with.

00:28:53.320 --> 00:28:56.320
Then obviously what is the
graph that your character has?

00:28:56.320 --> 00:28:57.940
And if it is just
one-dimensional,

00:28:57.940 --> 00:29:00.010
I usually kind of
stay away from it.

00:29:00.010 --> 00:29:03.880
But if it does have
layers and allows

00:29:03.880 --> 00:29:09.330
me to explore a new
expression, a new body language

00:29:09.330 --> 00:29:14.530
or allows me to bring anything
that would, A, surprise me,

00:29:14.530 --> 00:29:17.710
which would then
surprise my audience,

00:29:17.710 --> 00:29:21.010
is how I kind of like
to choose my work.

00:29:21.010 --> 00:29:24.460
And there's very little
work like that that happens,

00:29:24.460 --> 00:29:26.090
which would be only
based around you.

00:29:26.090 --> 00:29:30.100
So it's good to experiment with
parts that you can do in films.

00:29:30.100 --> 00:29:32.840
And then when you get
a film like "Daddy,"

00:29:32.840 --> 00:29:35.320
you get a lot of
layers and you get

00:29:35.320 --> 00:29:38.950
a lot of experience,
where you can put together

00:29:38.950 --> 00:29:42.460
many, many layers together
through your experience.

00:29:42.460 --> 00:29:45.010
So I guess, yeah,
that's how you do it.

00:29:45.010 --> 00:29:45.730
I like to do it.

00:29:45.730 --> 00:29:47.906
I get really bored
doing the same thing.

00:29:47.906 --> 00:29:49.780
You know, if you tell
me to do the same thing

00:29:49.780 --> 00:29:52.610
every single day, I
wouldn't be able to do it.

00:29:52.610 --> 00:29:54.520
So if it is to work
out in the same way

00:29:54.520 --> 00:29:59.685
or to go and meet the
same people everyday,

00:29:59.685 --> 00:30:01.324
no, it doesn't happen with me.

